{
  "$schema": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/oasis-tcs/sarif-spec/main/sarif-2.1/schema/sarif-schema-2.1.0.json",
  "version": "2.1.0",
  "runs": [
    {
      "tool": {
        "driver": {
          "name": "Tachi",
          "semanticVersion": "1.4",
          "informationUri": "https://github.com/example/tachi",
          "supportedTaxonomies": [
            { "name": "OWASP", "index": 0 },
            { "name": "CWE", "index": 1 }
          ],
          "rules": [
            {
              "id": "tachi/stride/spoofing",
              "shortDescription": { "text": "Identity spoofing threats" },
              "fullDescription": { "text": "Threats where an attacker assumes the identity of a legitimate user, service, or component. Covers credential theft, session hijacking, identity forgery, and impersonation of trusted agents or services." },
              "help": {
                "text": "Review authentication mechanisms, certificate validation, session management, and identity attestation across all inter-component communication paths.",
                "markdown": "**Detection Guidance**: Review authentication mechanisms, certificate validation, session management, and identity attestation.\n\n**References**: OWASP A07 (Identification and Authentication Failures), CWE-287 (Improper Authentication)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "tags": ["security", "stride", "spoofing", "authentication", "owasp", "cwe"],
                "security-severity": "9.0"
              },
              "relationships": [
                { "target": { "id": "A07", "toolComponent": { "name": "OWASP" } }, "kinds": ["relevant"] },
                { "target": { "id": "CWE-287", "toolComponent": { "name": "CWE" } }, "kinds": ["relevant"] }
              ]
            },
            {
              "id": "tachi/stride/tampering",
              "shortDescription": { "text": "Data tampering threats" },
              "fullDescription": { "text": "Threats where an attacker modifies data, code, or configuration. Covers data corruption, message tampering in transit, audit log manipulation, and training data poisoning." },
              "help": {
                "text": "Review data integrity controls, message signing, audit log append-only enforcement, and training data provenance.",
                "markdown": "**Detection Guidance**: Review data integrity controls, message signing, audit log append-only enforcement, and training data provenance.\n\n**References**: OWASP A08 (Software and Data Integrity Failures), CWE-345 (Insufficient Verification of Data Authenticity)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "tags": ["security", "stride", "tampering", "integrity", "owasp", "cwe"],
                "security-severity": "9.0"
              },
              "relationships": [
                { "target": { "id": "A08", "toolComponent": { "name": "OWASP" } }, "kinds": ["relevant"] },
                { "target": { "id": "CWE-345", "toolComponent": { "name": "CWE" } }, "kinds": ["relevant"] }
              ]
            },
            {
              "id": "tachi/stride/repudiation",
              "shortDescription": { "text": "Repudiation threats" },
              "fullDescription": { "text": "Threats where an attacker denies performing actions. Covers missing audit trails, insufficient logging, and accountability gaps in clinical AI workflows." },
              "help": {
                "text": "Review audit logging coverage, non-repudiable audit trail enforcement, and identity binding on all clinical actions.",
                "markdown": "**Detection Guidance**: Review audit logging coverage, non-repudiable audit trail enforcement, and identity binding.\n\n**References**: OWASP A09 (Security Logging and Monitoring Failures), CWE-778 (Insufficient Logging)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "tags": ["security", "stride", "repudiation", "audit", "logging", "owasp", "cwe"],
                "security-severity": "8.0"
              },
              "relationships": [
                { "target": { "id": "A09", "toolComponent": { "name": "OWASP" } }, "kinds": ["relevant"] },
                { "target": { "id": "CWE-778", "toolComponent": { "name": "CWE" } }, "kinds": ["relevant"] }
              ]
            },
            {
              "id": "tachi/stride/information-disclosure",
              "shortDescription": { "text": "Information disclosure threats" },
              "fullDescription": { "text": "Threats where sensitive data is exposed to unauthorized parties. Covers PHI leakage, model training data extraction, inter-agent channel eavesdropping, and inference request log exposure." },
              "help": {
                "text": "Review encryption at rest and in transit, access controls on sensitive data, PHI de-identification, and output filtering.",
                "markdown": "**Detection Guidance**: Review encryption at rest and in transit, access controls, PHI de-identification, and output filtering.\n\n**References**: OWASP A01 (Broken Access Control), CWE-200 (Exposure of Sensitive Information)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "tags": ["security", "stride", "information-disclosure", "data-exposure", "phi", "owasp", "cwe"],
                "security-severity": "9.0"
              },
              "relationships": [
                { "target": { "id": "A01", "toolComponent": { "name": "OWASP" } }, "kinds": ["relevant"] },
                { "target": { "id": "CWE-200", "toolComponent": { "name": "CWE" } }, "kinds": ["relevant"] }
              ]
            },
            {
              "id": "tachi/stride/denial-of-service",
              "shortDescription": { "text": "Denial of service threats" },
              "fullDescription": { "text": "Threats where availability is degraded or disrupted. Covers request floods, resource exhaustion, queue saturation, and multi-agent resource starvation." },
              "help": {
                "text": "Review rate limiting, circuit breakers, resource quotas, and capacity monitoring across all components.",
                "markdown": "**Detection Guidance**: Review rate limiting, circuit breakers, resource quotas, and capacity monitoring.\n\n**References**: OWASP A05 (Security Misconfiguration), CWE-400 (Uncontrolled Resource Consumption)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "tags": ["security", "stride", "denial-of-service", "availability", "owasp", "cwe"],
                "security-severity": "8.0"
              },
              "relationships": [
                { "target": { "id": "A05", "toolComponent": { "name": "OWASP" } }, "kinds": ["relevant"] },
                { "target": { "id": "CWE-400", "toolComponent": { "name": "CWE" } }, "kinds": ["relevant"] }
              ]
            },
            {
              "id": "tachi/stride/elevation-of-privilege",
              "shortDescription": { "text": "Privilege escalation threats" },
              "fullDescription": { "text": "Threats where an attacker gains higher access than authorized. Covers RBAC bypass, FHIR scope escalation, orchestrator privilege abuse, and tool chain escalation." },
              "help": {
                "text": "Review per-component authorization, least-privilege enforcement, FHIR resource scoping, and tool call permission boundaries.",
                "markdown": "**Detection Guidance**: Review per-component authorization, least-privilege enforcement, FHIR resource scoping, and tool call permission boundaries.\n\n**References**: OWASP A01 (Broken Access Control), CWE-269 (Improper Privilege Management)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "tags": ["security", "stride", "privilege-escalation", "authorization", "owasp", "cwe"],
                "security-severity": "9.0"
              },
              "relationships": [
                { "target": { "id": "A01", "toolComponent": { "name": "OWASP" } }, "kinds": ["relevant"] },
                { "target": { "id": "CWE-269", "toolComponent": { "name": "CWE" } }, "kinds": ["relevant"] }
              ]
            },
            {
              "id": "tachi/ai/agentic-threats",
              "shortDescription": { "text": "AI agent autonomy and misuse threats" },
              "fullDescription": { "text": "Threats from autonomous AI agent behavior, tool abuse, and multi-agent coordination exploitation. Covers unconstrained autonomous actions, MCP tool chain attacks, inter-agent message flooding, and agentic pattern exploitation." },
              "help": {
                "text": "Review agent action scope limits, tool call authorization, inter-agent authentication, and human-in-the-loop gates for high-consequence actions.",
                "markdown": "**Detection Guidance**: Review agent action scope limits, tool call authorization, inter-agent authentication, and HITL gates.\n\n**References**: OWASP Agentic Security Initiative (ASI), MITRE ATLAS, CWE-693 (Protection Mechanism Failure)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "tags": ["security", "ai", "agentic", "autonomy", "tool-use", "multi-agent", "cwe"],
                "security-severity": "9.0"
              },
              "relationships": [
                { "target": { "id": "CWE-693", "toolComponent": { "name": "CWE" } }, "kinds": ["relevant"] }
              ]
            },
            {
              "id": "tachi/ai/llm-threats",
              "shortDescription": { "text": "LLM-specific threats" },
              "fullDescription": { "text": "Threats specific to large language model components. Covers prompt injection, training data poisoning via feedback loops, model extraction, and membership inference attacks on fine-tuned clinical models." },
              "help": {
                "text": "Review prompt sanitization, training data provenance, model output validation, membership inference defenses, and fine-tuning pipeline integrity.",
                "markdown": "**Detection Guidance**: Review prompt sanitization, training data provenance, model output validation, and fine-tuning pipeline integrity.\n\n**References**: OWASP LLM01:2025 (Prompt Injection), OWASP LLM03:2025 (Training Data Poisoning), OWASP LLM10:2025 (Model Theft), CWE-74 (Improper Neutralization of Special Elements in Output)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "tags": ["security", "ai", "llm", "prompt-injection", "data-poisoning", "model-theft", "cwe"],
                "security-severity": "9.0"
              },
              "relationships": [
                { "target": { "id": "CWE-74", "toolComponent": { "name": "CWE" } }, "kinds": ["relevant"] }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      "taxonomies": [
        {
          "name": "OWASP",
          "version": "2021",
          "informationUri": "https://owasp.org/Top10/",
          "organization": "OWASP Foundation",
          "shortDescription": { "text": "OWASP Top 10 Web Application Security Risks" }
        },
        {
          "name": "CWE",
          "version": "4.13",
          "informationUri": "https://cwe.mitre.org/",
          "organization": "MITRE",
          "shortDescription": { "text": "Common Weakness Enumeration" }
        }
      ],
      "results": [
        {
          "ruleId": "tachi/stride/spoofing",
          "message": { "text": "An attacker may impersonate a legitimate physician by replaying or forging clinical query credentials, gaining unauthorized access to clinical recommendation views and patient data.", "markdown": "Implement mutual TLS authentication and short-lived signed JWT tokens with physician identity binding. Enforce step-up authentication for high-sensitivity clinical queries." },
          "level": "error",
          "locations": [{ "physicalLocation": { "artifactLocation": { "uri": "examples/maestro-reference/architecture.md" }, "region": { "startLine": 1 } }, "logicalLocations": [{ "name": "Physician", "fullyQualifiedName": "External Zone/Physician", "kind": "external-entity" }] }],
